          Create new launch template
          Launch Template Description
          Fleet Composition
          The launch template determines the instance type and purchase option (On-Demand or Spot).
          Choose a mix of On-Demand Instances and Spot Instances and multiple instance types. Spot Instances are automatically launched at the lowest price available.
          Instance Types
          Add acceptable instance types to your fleet. Change their order to set the launch priority of On-Demand Instances. This order does not affect Spot Instances.
          Add a minimum of two instance types
          Instances Distribution
          • Launch On-Demand Instances based on the above priority order.
          • Diversify Spot Instances across your 2 lowest priced instance types per Availability Zone.
          • Set your maximum Spot price for each instance type to equal the On-Demand price.
          • Maintain a mix of 70% On-Demand Instances and 30% Spot Instances.
          On-Demand Allocation Strategy
          Prioritized
          Maximum Spot Price
          Default uses current Spot price, but caps it at the On-Demand price.
          Spot Allocation Strategy
          Diversify Spot Instances across your lowest priced instance types per Availability Zone
          Optional On-Demand Base
          Designate the first instances as On-Demand
          On-Demand Percentage Above Base
          % On-Demand and 30% Spot

              Monitoring
              Amazon EC2 Detailed Monitoring metrics, which are provided at 1 minute frequency, are not enabled for the launch configuration Auto-Scaling-DBS-Rewards-Demo-Web. Instances launched from it will use Basic Monitoring metrics, provided at 5 minute frequency.
